title: Chelsea vs Liverpool -English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
title_en_trans: Chelsea vs Liverpool -English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
synopsis: After their 3-1 win in May, Chelsea could enjoy back-to-back league wins over Liverpool for the first time since November 2014. synopsis: ATP 250 European Open 2025 (10th edition) debuts in Brussels after nine years in Antwerp, staged on indoor-hard courts at Brussels Expo (Palais 12), 13–19 Oct. Draw sizes: 28-player singles / 16-team doubles. Prize money: €706,850. Expect fast, first-strike tennis, sharp returns and tie-break pressure as contenders fight for late-season ranking points and momentum toward Turin.

title: Race 2 - World Super Bike - Estoril Round 2025
title_en_trans: Race 2 - World Super Bike - Estoril Round 2025
synopsis: WorldSBK heads to Estoril for the weekend’s decisive Race 2. The long front straight and technical infield reward grip and bravery, with braking into Parabólica and the drag to Turn 1 often settling it. Expect drafting trains, tyre-management gambles, and late lunges as title hopes to tighten in a full-throttle finale.

synopsis: After their 3-1 win in May, Chelsea could enjoy back-to-back league wins over Liverpool for the first time since November 2014. Liverpool are winless in their last four Premier League games at Stamford Bridge  and could lose away to Chelsea two seasons running in the league for the first time since losing three on the bounce from 2004-05 to 2006-07.

synopsis: Buriram United are unbeaten in their three AFC Champions League Elite matches against Johor Darul Ta’zim, with the only goal scored in those matches coming in the most recent such game. Buriram United have only lost two of their nine AFC Champions League Elite season opening matches, winning three and drawing four such games; unbeaten in their last three games in the group stage of the competition, a win or a draw here will see them go unbeaten in four consecutive such games for the first time since 2018.

title: My Faith in Sport - Ummah
synopsis:
Ummah is an Arabic word meaning "community” – an important concept in Islam as it encourages Muslims to support and help each other especially in times of need. Zakat is one of the most important aspects in Islam - it is the principle of giving back to a community/person that needs it more than you. 
This episode will look into Zakat around footballers Ali-Al Hamadi and Nadia Nadim and the role it plays in their lives. Al-Hamadi is the first Iraqi to play in the Premier League with a remarkable back story – his family escaped persecution in their homeland in the early 2000s before settling, as refugees, in Liverpool. synopsis: ATP 250 European Open 2025 (10th edition) debuts in Brussels after nine years in Antwerp, staged on indoor-hard courts at Brussels Expo (Palais 12), 13–19 Oct. Draw sizes: 28-player singles / 16-team doubles. Prize money: €706,850. Expect fast, first-strike tennis, sharp returns and tie-break pressure as contenders fight for late-season ranking points and momentum toward Turin.

title_en_trans: Raphael COLLIGNON (BEL) vs Francisco COMESANA (ARG) - ATP 250 - European open 2025 - Brussels
synopsis: ATP 250 European Open 2025 (10th edition) debuts in Brussels after nine years in Antwerp, staged on indoor-hard courts at Brussels Expo (Palais 12), 13–19 Oct. Draw sizes: 28-player singles / 16-team doubles. Prize money: €706,850. Expect fast, first-strike tennis, sharp returns and tie-break pressure as contenders fight for late-season ranking points and momentum toward Turin.

title: Nîmes vs Nantes - LNH Division 1 - French Handball Starligue
title_en_trans: Nîmes vs Nantes - LNH Division 1 - French Handball Starligue
synopsis: Dive into the excitement of French handball with Liqui Moly Starligue, formerly LNH Division 1. Established in 1952, this premier league event features 16 top teams battling for glory. With Montpellier’s  14 Handball titles and Paris Saint-Germain's 11 wins, the competition is fierce. Champions earn spots in the EHF Champions League, while cup winners qualify for the European League.

title: Race 1 - Formula 4 Italy - Misano Round - 2025
synopsis: The Misano weekend opens with a sprint that rewards clean starts, tyre warm-up and bravery through Curvone. Expect late dives into Turn 1, heavy braking at Quercia and traction duels out of Tramonto onto the back straight. Safety cars and track-limits calls can flip the order, while newcomers hunt points and title hopefuls set the tone for the round.

title: Race 2 - Formula 4 Italy - Misano Round - 2025
synopsis: Race 2 reshuffles the deck after overnight tweaks. Warmer track temps raise tyre-degradation stakes, making slipstream timing on the main straight vital. Inside lines at Turn 1 and measured exits from Tramonto decide most passes. Watch for undercuts on out-laps, safety-car restarts, and penalties for track limits as contenders bank crucial mid-round points.

title: M1- ATP 250 - European open 2025 - Brussels
synopsis: ATP 250 European Open 2025 (10th edition) debuts in Brussels after nine years in Antwerp, staged on indoor-hard courts at Brussels Expo (Palais 12), 13–19 Oct. Draw sizes: 28-player singles / 16-team doubles. Prize money: €706,850. Expect fast, first-strike tennis, sharp returns and tie-break pressure as contenders fight for late-season ranking points and momentum toward Turin.

title: Arsenal vs West Ham United - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
title_en_trans: Arsenal vs West Ham United - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
synopsis: Arsenal have lost both of their last two home league games against West Ham, only ever losing three in a row once before. West Ham United are looking to become only the second side to win three successive Premier League away games against Arsenal, after Manchester City, who won six on the bounce from March 2018 to February 2023.

title: Race 4 - Formula 4 Italy - Misano Round - 2025
synopsis: The Misano finale. Championship hopefuls chase maximum points as fatigue, tyre life and track limits shape the last attacks. Anticipate safety-car drama, photo-finish drafts to the stripe, and decisive moves under pressure as the round closes with a flat-out sprint.

title: Yannick HANFMANN (GER) vs Matteo ARNALDI (ITA) - ATP 250 - European open 2025 - Brussels
title_en_trans: Yannick HANFMANN (GER) vs Matteo ARNALDI (ITA) - ATP 250 - European open 2025 - Brussels
synopsis: ATP 250 European Open 2025 (10th edition) debuts in Brussels after nine years in Antwerp, staged on indoor-hard courts at Brussels Expo (Palais 12), 13–19 Oct. Draw sizes: 28-player singles / 16-team doubles. Prize money: €706,850. Expect fast, first-strike tennis, sharp returns and tie-break pressure as contenders fight for late-season ranking points and momentum toward Turin.

title: Race 5 - Formula 4 Italy - Misano Round - 2025
synopsis: Rising talents go wheel-to-wheel at Misano World Circuit Marco Simoncelli in Race 5. Slipstreams on the main straight and commitment through Curvone shape the order, while track limits, safety cars, and bold restarts can flip everything late. A flat-out sprint where newcomers and title hopefuls fight to the flag.

title: My Faith in Sport - Taffakur
synopsis: Islam teaches Muslims about ‘Tawakkul’ meaning trusting in God’s plan. Muslims believe in the idea that with anything in life we put forward our best efforts but ultimately the rest is left to God and believing whatever the outcome, it was pre-written. Omar Marmoush is the feature athlete in the final episode of the series – from the outskirts of the Eintracht Frankfurt side to an $80m move to Premier League Manchester City, his last 18 months has seen an incredible rise. His love of Ramadan and belief that fasting elevates his game is a central theme of the final episode alongside detail of his early life, career and his unfaltering belief in Islam. The series concludes with all athletes re

title: Chelsea vs. Liverpool - English Premier League 2025/2026

synopsis: After their 3-1 win in May, Chelsea could enjoy back-to-back league wins over Liverpool for the first time since November 2014. Liverpool are winless in their last four Premier League games at Stamford Bridge  and could lose away to Chelsea two seasons running in the league for the first time since losing three on the bounce from 2004-05 to 2006-07.

title: Race - Qiddiya Round - Extreme H World Cup 2025
title_en_trans: Race - Qiddiya Round - Extreme H World Cup 2025
synopsis: Extreme H World Cup hits Qiddiya for a desert race. Hydrogen-powered Pioneer 25 SUVs face Time Trials, head-to-head heats, and a multi-car Grand Final, with energy management, tyre wear and route choice deciding positions. Expect dunes, dust and daring passes under the Tuwaiq cliffs, driver switches, and strategy on boost usage as teams chase points, manufacturer bragging rights and momentum in the sport’s new zero-emissions era. Broadcast highlights and on-board shots bring the action home.

synopsis: Northern Ireland are winless in their last 13 matches against Germany, losing the last 10 in a row. They last beat them back in November 1983 in a European Championship qualifier. Germany have won seven of their nine away matches against Northern Ireland, winning the last five in a row and scoring 15 goals in the process. Their most recent visit was a 2-0 win in September 2019 in a European Championship qualifier.

title: Paris FC vs Lorient - Ligue 1 2025/2026 Week 7

synopsis: Paris FC beat Lorient 3-2 in March 2025  after failing to win any of their first seven meetings in all competitions against them this century. title: Al Ahli Saudi FC (KSA) vs PFC Nasaf (UZB) - AFC Champions League Elite 2025/2026 - West MD1
title_en_trans: Al Ahli Saudi FC (KSA) vs PFC Nasaf (UZB) - AFC Champions League Elite 2025/2026 - West MD1
synopsis: This will be the fifth AFC Champions League Elite meeting between Al-Ahli and Nasaf, with Nasaf’s only win coming in their most recent such game on 2 March 2016 ; Al-Ahli’s most recent game in the competition against Uzbek opposition was a 2-1 win over Pakhtakor Tashkent on 20 May 2019, a win here will see them win two consecutive such games for the first time in competition history. Al-Ahli are unbeaten in each of their last 18 AFC Champions League Elite games, including the final of the 2024-25 edition ; avoiding defeat here will see them equal Gamba Osaka for the joint third-longest such run in the competition.

title: Everton vs Crystal Palace - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
title_en_trans: Everton vs Crystal Palace - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
synopsis: Everton have lost just one of their last 21 Premier League meetings with Crystal Palace, a 1-3 defeat in December 2021. Indeed, among all sides they have faced 20+ times in the competition, their points-per-game rate of 1.81 against the Eagles is bettered only against West Brom. Crystal Palace are winless in each of their last 10 Premier League away games against Everton  since a 3-2 victory in September 2014 under Neil Warnock.

title: M1- ATP 250 - European open 2025 - Brussels
synopsis: ATP 250 European Open 2025 (10th edition) debuts in Brussels after nine years in Antwerp, staged on indoor-hard courts at Brussels Expo (Palais 12), 13–19 Oct. Draw sizes: 28-player singles / 16-team doubles. Prize money: €706,850. Expect fast, first-strike tennis, sharp returns and tie-break pressure as contenders fight for late-season ranking points and momentum toward Turin.

title: Nîmes vs Nantes - LNH Division 1 - French Handball Starligue
title_en_trans: Nîmes vs Nantes - LNH Division 1 - French Handball Starligue
synopsis: Dive into the excitement of French handball with Liqui Moly Starligue, formerly LNH Division 1. Established in 1952, this premier league event features 16 top teams battling for glory. With Montpellier’s  14 Handball titles and Paris Saint-Germain's 11 wins, the competition is fierce. Champions earn spots in the EHF Champions League, while cup winners qualify for the European League.

title: Al Shorta (IRQ) vs Al Sadd SC (QAT) - AFC Champions League Elite 2025/2026 - West MD1
title_en_trans: Al Shorta (IRQ) vs Al Sadd SC (QAT) - AFC Champions League Elite 2025/2026 - West MD1
synopsis: This will be the first ever AFC Champions League Elite meeting between Al Shorta and Al Sadd; Iraqi teams have won five of their last seven matches against Qatari sides in the competition, after winning just one of the first seven. title: PALESTINE, ONE JERSEY, MANY ROOTS
synopsis: Story of the Palestinian national football team, a team that is far more than the sum of its players. Separated by borders, by checkpoints, and exile, the tells is inspiring “One Jersey…Many Roots” them is a single jersey, a shared dream, and a deep sense of responsibility to players come from every corner of Palestine and from communities scattered across the globe. What unites represent their people on and off the pitch that Palestine endures. This is not just in every match, they carry not just a ball but the weight of history, identity and hope. Fot their supporters, each goal is a voice, each victory a declaration. Football it s a living emblem of unity, resilience and the unbreakable b

synopsis: After their 3-1 win in May, Chelsea could enjoy back-to-back league wins over Liverpool for the first time since November 2014. title: Race 1 - Formula 4 Italy - Misano Round - 2025
synopsis: The Misano weekend opens with a sprint that rewards clean starts, tyre warm-up and bravery through Curvone. Expect late dives into Turn 1, heavy braking at Quercia and traction duels out of Tramonto onto the back straight. Safety cars and track-limits calls can flip the order, while newcomers hunt points and title hopefuls set the tone for the round.

title: Lille vs PSG - French Ligue 1 2025/2026 Week 7
title_en_trans: Lille vs PSG - French Ligue 1 2025/2026 Week 7
synopsis: Lille have won just one of their last 13 home Ligue 1 games against Paris SG, a 5-1 victory on 14 April 2019, which remains Paris Saint-Germain's biggest away defeat in the top-flight in the 21st century. Lille have lost their last two Ligue 1 matches and could suffer three consecutive defeats in the competition for the first time since December 2019-January 2020. Lille could also fail to score in three consecutive Ligue 1 games for the first time since September 2017.

synopsis:
The biggest names from across Asia will celebrate a fantastic year of football.
The 29th edition of the annual gala ceremony will recognise the continent’s finest across a total of 20 categories, including the prestigious Male & Female AFC Player of the Year awards.
Hosted in the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia for the first time, the event will be staged at the King Fahad Cultural Center, Riyadh.

title_en_trans: Chelsea vs Benfica - UEFA Champions League 2025/26 - MD2
synopsis: Chelsea have won all four of their competitive meetings with Benfica, with the most recent of those coming earlier this year at the FIFA Club World Cup. This will be the first meeting between Chelsea and Benfica in the group/league phase of a competition, with the previous four all having come in the knockout stages: UEFA Champions League quarter-finals in 2011-12, UEFA Europa League final in 2012-13 and the FIFA Club World Cup last 16 earlier this year.

title: Race 3 - Formula 4 Italy - Misano Round - 2025
synopsis: With setups refined, Race 3 is often the weekend’s fiercest sprint. Nose-to-tail packs form into Turn 1, while rhythm and patience through the fast right-lefts keep front tyres alive. Curvone commitment and a tidy run to Quercia create overtaking chances. Expect bold moves, defensive elbows, and strategy on push laps to climb

title: Race 4 - Formula 4 Italy - Misano Round - 2025
synopsis: The Misano finale. Championship hopefuls chase maximum points as fatigue, tyre life and track limits shape the last attacks. A strong launch, disciplined braking at Quercia and perfect traction from Tramonto decide podiums. Anticipate safety-car drama, photo-finish drafts to the stripe, and decisive moves under pressure as the round closes with a flat-out sprint.

title: Race 5 - Formula 4 Italy - Misano Round - 2025
synopsis: Rising talents go wheel-to-wheel at Misano World Circuit Marco Simoncelli in Race 5. Slipstreams on the main straight and commitment through Curvone shape the order, while track limits, safety cars, and bold restarts can flip everything late. A flat-out sprint where newcomers and title hopefuls fight to the flag.

title: Gold Standard Ep6
synopsis:
"A Farewell to Legends" – France 2017
France’s 2017 victory on home soil was both a celebration and a goodbye to legends like Omeyer and Narcisse. 
This emotional win against Norway secured their sixth title and closed a golden chapter in French handball.

title_en_trans: Latvia vs England - UEFA European Qualifiers World Cup 2026 - MD8
synopsis: This will be the second meeting between Latvia and England, with the first coming in March this year when the Three Lions won 3-0 at Wembley with goals from Reece James, Harry Kane and Eberechi Eze. Latvia will be the 72nd nation England have played an away match against – they’ve won their last three first time away games against a nation.

title: M1- ATP 250 - European open 2025 - Brussels
synopsis: ATP 250 European Open 2025 (10th edition) debuts in Brussels after nine years in Antwerp, staged on indoor-hard courts at Brussels Expo (Palais 12), 13–19 Oct. Draw sizes: 28-player singles / 16-team doubles. Prize money: €706,850. Expect fast, first-strike tennis, sharp returns and tie-break pressure as contenders fight for late-season ranking points and momentum toward Turin.

title: Gold Standard Ep6
synopsis:
"A Farewell to Legends" – France 2017
France’s 2017 victory on home soil was both a celebration and a goodbye to legends like Omeyer and Narcisse. 
This emotional win against Norway secured their sixth title and closed a golden chapter in French handball.

title: Latvia vs England - UEFA European Qualifiers World Cup 2026 - MD8
title_en_trans: Latvia vs England - UEFA European Qualifiers World Cup 2026 - MD8
synopsis: This will be the second meeting between Latvia and England, with the first coming in March this year when the Three Lions won 3-0 at Wembley with goals from Reece James, Harry Kane and Eberechi Eze. Latvia will be the 72nd nation England have played an away match against – they’ve won their last three first time away games against a nation.

title: M1- ATP 250 - European open 2025 - Brussels
synopsis: ATP 250 European Open 2025 (10th edition) debuts in Brussels after nine years in Antwerp, staged on indoor-hard courts at Brussels Expo (Palais 12), 13–19 Oct. Draw sizes: 28-player singles / 16-team doubles. Prize money: €706,850. Expect fast, first-strike tennis, sharp returns and tie-break pressure as contenders fight for late-season ranking points and momentum toward Turin.

synopsis: ATP 250 European Open 2025 (10th edition) debuts in Brussels after nine years in Antwerp, staged on indoor-hard courts at Brussels Expo (Palais 12), 13–19 Oct. Draw sizes: 28-player singles / 16-team doubles. Prize money: €706,850. Expect fast, first-strike tennis, sharp returns and tie-break pressure as contenders fight for late-season ranking points and momentum toward Turin.

title: My Faith in Sport - Sawm
synopsis: Ramadan is a crucial period in the Islamic calendar but fasting (Sawm) can provide complications for athletes who are trying to compete at the highest level. But to what extent is fasting a negative or can it actually aid performance? We look at the life and adaptation throughout Ramadan of Adam Azim – an unbeaten professional boxer from the UK, Fares El Bakh – a weightlifter who won Qatar’s first ever Olympic gold medal, and Zainab Alema – a rugby player who is aiming to become the first player to represent England wearing a hijab. Experts in Sports Science and Nutrition from Aspetar Clinic, Qatar also add detail of the physical impact athletes encounter during Ramadan.

title: Leeds United vs. Tottenham Hotspur - English Premier League 2025/2026
title_en_trans: Leeds United vs. Tottenham Hotspur - English Premier League 2025/2026
synopsis: Leeds United have lost nine of their last 11 Premier League games against Tottenham Hotspur, including each of their last four in a row – their longest ever league losing run to Spurs. Tottenham have won both of their last two league visits to Elland Road and could beat Leeds United away from home three times running in the league for the very first time.

title: Scotland vs Belarus - UEFA European Qualifiers World Cup 2026 - MD8
title_en_trans: Scotland vs Belarus - UEFA European Qualifiers World Cup 2026 - MD8
synopsis: Scotland have won three of their previous five meetings with Belarus, with each of those coming in World Cup qualifying – the most recent was just last month, with the Scots winning 2-0 in Belarus. This will be Belarus’ third trip to face Scotland, losing the first 4-1 in September 1997 before winning the most recent 1-0 in October 2005.

title: M1- ATP 250 - European open 2025 - Brussels
synopsis: ATP 250 European Open 2025 (10th edition) debuts in Brussels after nine years in Antwerp, staged on indoor-hard courts at Brussels Expo (Palais 12), 13–19 Oct. Draw sizes: 28-player singles / 16-team doubles. Prize money: €706,850. Expect fast, first-strike tennis, sharp returns and tie-break pressure as contenders fight for late-season ranking points and momentum toward Turin.

title: Chelsea vs. Liverpool - English Premier League 2025/2026
title_en_trans: Chelsea vs. Liverpool - English Premier League 2025/2026
synopsis: After their 3-1 win in May, Chelsea could enjoy back-to-back league wins over Liverpool for the first time since November 2014. Liverpool are winless in their last four Premier League games at Stamford Bridge  and could lose away to Chelsea two seasons running in the league for the first time since losing three on the bounce from 2004-05 to 2006-07.

title: Leeds United vs Tottenham Hotspur - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8

title: M1- ATP 250 - European open 2025 - Brussels
synopsis: ATP 250 European Open 2025 (10th edition) debuts in Brussels after nine years in Antwerp, staged on indoor-hard courts at Brussels Expo (Palais 12), 13–19 Oct. Draw sizes: 28-player singles / 16-team doubles. Prize money: €706,850. Expect fast, first-strike tennis, sharp returns and tie-break pressure as contenders fight for late-season ranking points and momentum toward Turin.

synopsis: Olympique Lyonnais are unbeaten in their last 17 Ligue 1 matches against Toulouse FC, a longer run in the top-flight has only been recorded against Saint-Étienne. synopsis: World No.1 pairing Gemma Triay/Delfina Brea face No.2 Ariana Sánchez/Paula Josemaría at Rotterdam Ahoy. title: Johor Darul Ta’zim FC (MAS) vs FC Machida Zelvia (JPN) - AFC Champions League Elite 2025/2026 - East
title_en_trans: Johor Darul Ta’zim FC (MAS) vs FC Machida Zelvia (JPN) - AFC Champions League Elite 2025/2026 - East
synopsis: Johor Darul Ta’zim will be playing against Machida Zelvia for the first time in AFC Champions League history; Johor Darul Ta’zim are winless in their last seven games in the competition against teams from Japan, failing to score in each of the last five of these games. Machida Zelvia are the fifth Japanese club to start their debut AFC Champions League Elite campaign with a draw ; the last two such participants gained at least one point in their second game.

title: Al Hilal SFC (KSA) vs Al Duhail SC (QAT) - AFC Champions League Elite 2025/2026 - West MD1
title_en_trans: Al Hilal SFC (KSA) vs Al Duhail SC (QAT) - AFC Champions League Elite 2025/2026 - West MD1
synopsis: Al Duhail won their first AFC Champions League Elite meeting with Al-Hilal, but Al-Hilal are unbeaten in the six since, including their joint-biggest win in the competition  – Al Duhail’s heaviest defeat in the tournament. Qatari teams have lost their last five matches against Saudi sides in the competition; their last win was Al Sadd’s 2-1 victory over Al-Nassr in December 2014. Qatari teams have lost more matches  and conceded more goals  against Saudi teams than against any other nation.

title: Everton vs Crystal Palace - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
title_en_trans: Everton vs Crystal Palace - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
synopsis: Everton have lost just one of their last 21 Premier League meetings with Crystal Palace, a 1-3 defeat in December 2021. Indeed, among all sides they have faced 20+ times in the competition, their points-per-game rate of 1.81 against the Eagles is bettered only against West Brom. Crystal Palace are winless in each of their last 10 Premier League away games against Everton  since a 3-2 victory in September 2014 under Neil Warnock.

title: M1- ATP 250 - European open 2025 - Brussels
synopsis: ATP 250 European Open 2025 (10th edition) debuts in Brussels after nine years in Antwerp, staged on indoor-hard courts at Brussels Expo (Palais 12), 13–19 Oct. Draw sizes: 28-player singles / 16-team doubles. Prize money: €706,850. Expect fast, first-strike tennis, sharp returns and tie-break pressure as contenders fight for late-season ranking points and momentum toward Turin.

title: Arturo Coello (ESP) / Agustin Tapia (ARG) vs  Federico Chingotto (ARG) / Alejandro Galan (ESP) - Men

synopsis: Top seeds Arturo Coello/Agustín Tapia clash with No.2 Alejandro Galán/Federico Chingotto. Coello/Tapia dominated most of 2025, but Galán/Chingotto struck back with victory in Germany P2. title: Qatar vs UAE - AFC Asian Qualifiers Road To 26 Playoffs - MD3 - Mini Match
title_en_trans: Qatar vs UAE - AFC Asian Qualifiers Road To 26 Playoffs - MD3 - Mini Match
synopsis:
The fourth round of AFC 2026 FIFA World Cup Qualification matches take place over three days.
The third-placed and fourth-placed teams from the third round were divided into two groups of three teams.
Group A features Qatar, UAE & Oman and will play their matches in Qatar.
Group B Features KSA, Iraq & Indonesia who will play their games in KSA.
The winners of each group will qualify directly for the 2026 FIFA World Cup, while the runners-up will advance to the fifth round.

title: M1- ATP 250 - European open 2025 - Brussels
synopsis: ATP 250 European Open 2025 (10th edition) debuts in Brussels after nine years in Antwerp, staged on indoor-hard courts at Brussels Expo (Palais 12), 13–19 Oct. Draw sizes: 28-player singles / 16-team doubles. Prize money: €706,850. Expect fast, first-strike tennis, sharp returns and tie-break pressure as contenders fight for late-season ranking points and momentum toward Turin.

title: Leeds United vs. Tottenham Hotspur - English Premier League 2025/2026
title_en_trans: Leeds United vs. Tottenham Hotspur - English Premier League 2025/2026
synopsis: Leeds United have lost nine of their last 11 Premier League games against Tottenham Hotspur, including each of their last four in a row – their longest ever league losing run to Spurs. Tottenham have won both of their last two league visits to Elland Road and could beat Leeds United away from home three times running in the league for the very first time.

title_en_trans: Monaco vs Nice - French Ligue 1 2025/2026 Week 7
synopsis: Monaco will face OGC Nice for the 131st time in all competitions. Monaco have recorded 58 wins against OGC Nice, a figure they have only achieved against Lyon and Rennes. OGC Nice, in turn, have lost to Monaco 58 times in all competitions, with only defeats against Marseille  being more frequent. Monaco have lost three of their last five Ligue 1 matches against Nice, as many defeats as in their previous 12 encounters with OGCN.

title: M1- ATP 250 - European open 2025 - Brussels
synopsis: ATP 250 European Open 2025 (10th edition) debuts in Brussels after nine years in Antwerp, staged on indoor-hard courts at Brussels Expo (Palais 12), 13–19 Oct. Draw sizes: 28-player singles / 16-team doubles. Prize money: €706,850. Expect fast, first-strike tennis, sharp returns and tie-break pressure as contenders fight for late-season ranking points and momentum toward Turin.

title: Chelsea vs. Liverpool - English Premier League 2025/2026
title_en_trans: Chelsea vs. Liverpool - English Premier League 2025/2026
synopsis: After their 3-1 win in May, Chelsea could enjoy back-to-back league wins over Liverpool for the first time since November 2014. Liverpool are winless in their last four Premier League games at Stamford Bridge  and could lose away to Chelsea two seasons running in the league for the first time since losing three on the bounce from 2004-05 to 2006-07.

title: M1 -ATP 250 - European open 2025 - Brussels
synopsis: ATP 250 European Open 2025 (10th edition) debuts in Brussels after nine years in Antwerp, staged on indoor-hard courts at Brussels Expo (Palais 12), 13–19 Oct. Draw sizes: 28-player singles / 16-team doubles. Prize money: €706,850. Expect fast, first-strike tennis, sharp returns and tie-break pressure as contenders fight for late-season ranking points and momentum toward Turin.

title: Qatar vs UAE - AFC Asian Qualifiers Road To 26 Playoffs - MD3 - Mini Match
title_en_trans: Qatar vs UAE - AFC Asian Qualifiers Road To 26 Playoffs - MD3 - Mini Match
synopsis:
The fourth round of AFC 2026 FIFA World Cup Qualification matches take place over three days.
The third-placed and fourth-placed teams from the third round were divided into two groups of three teams.
Group A features Qatar, UAE & Oman and will play their matches in Qatar.
Group B Features KSA, Iraq & Indonesia who will play their games in KSA.
The winners of each group will qualify directly for the 2026 FIFA World Cup, while the runners-up will advance to the fifth round.

title: One Friday Fight -129
synopsis: ONE Friday Fights 129 lights up Bangkok on Oct 17 with 12 bouts across Muay Thai, MMA, and kickboxing. Expect fireworks in the headliner as Thailand’s Tengnueng collides with Myanmar’s Tun Min Aung in a KO-hungry showdown. Plus, standout clashes: Petlampun vs Ayad Albadr, and 19-year-old Fergus Smith vs Zahran Al-Wesabi. Live from Lumpinee Boxing Stadium, its elbows, knees, and spinning kicks all night in a stacked showcase. Prelims spotlight rising prospects; main card promises fast finishes.

title: Lille vs PSG - French Ligue 1 2025/2026 Week 7
title_en_trans: Lille vs PSG - French Ligue 1 2025/2026 Week 7
synopsis: Lille have won just one of their last 13 home Ligue 1 games against Paris SG, a 5-1 victory on 14 April 2019, which remains Paris Saint-Germain's biggest away defeat in the top-flight in the 21st century. Lille have lost their last two Ligue 1 matches and could suffer three consecutive defeats in the competition for the first time since December 2019-January 2020. Lille could also fail to score in three consecutive Ligue 1 games for the first time since September 2017.

title: Brentford vs. Manchester City - English Premier League 2025/2026

Manchester City have only lost one of their four Premier League visits to Brentford, going down 1-0 on the final day of the 2022-23 season.

title: M2 -ATP 250 - European open 2025 - Brussels
synopsis: ATP 250 European Open 2025 (10th edition) debuts in Brussels after nine years in Antwerp, staged on indoor-hard courts at Brussels Expo (Palais 12), 13–19 Oct. Draw sizes: 28-player singles / 16-team doubles. Prize money: €706,850. Expect fast, first-strike tennis, sharp returns and tie-break pressure as contenders fight for late-season ranking points and momentum toward Turin.

synopsis: The Qatari League is the official football league in Qatar. The league includes 12 teams. The most famous participating clubs are Al-Sadd, the champions of the last season; Al-Rayyan and Al-Arabi, the popular teams, Al-Duhail and Al-Gharafa, serious contenders for the title every season. The Qatari league includes star names such as Firmino, Verratti, and Qatari Akram Afif, the best player in Asia.

title: Chelsea vs. Liverpool - English Premier League 2025/2026
title_en_trans: Chelsea vs. Liverpool - English Premier League 2025/2026
synopsis: After their 3-1 win in May, Chelsea could enjoy back-to-back league wins over Liverpool for the first time since November 2014. Liverpool are winless in their last four Premier League games at Stamford Bridge  and could lose away to Chelsea two seasons running in the league for the first time since losing three on the bounce from 2004-05 to 2006-07.

synopsis: Dive into the excitement of French handball with Liqui Moly Starligue, formerly LNH Division 1. Established in 1952, this premier league event features 16 top teams battling for glory. Champions earn spots in the EHF Champions League, while cup winners qualify for the European League.

title: Arsenal vs West Ham United - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8

title: M1 -ATP 250 - European open 2025 - Brussels
synopsis: ATP 250 European Open 2025 (10th edition) debuts in Brussels after nine years in Antwerp, staged on indoor-hard courts at Brussels Expo (Palais 12), 13–19 Oct. Draw sizes: 28-player singles / 16-team doubles. Prize money: €706,850. title: Race 2 - World Super Bike - Estoril Round 2025
title_en_trans: Race 2 - World Super Bike - Estoril Round 2025
synopsis: WorldSBK heads to Estoril for the weekend’s decisive Race 2. The long front straight and technical infield reward grip and bravery, with braking into Parabólica and the drag to Turn 1 often settling it. Expect drafting trains, tyre-management gambles, and late lunges as title hopes to tighten in a full-throttle finale.

synopsis: Dive into the excitement of French handball with Liqui Moly Starligue, formerly LNH Division 1. Established in 1952, this premier league event features 16 top teams battling for glory. With Montpellier’s  14 Handball titles and Paris Saint-Germain's 11 wins, the competition is fierce. Champions earn spots in the EHF Champions League, while cup winners qualify for the European League.

synopsis: This will be the first fixture in AFC Champions League Elite between Nasaf and Al-Hilal, Nasaf have won just one of their eight games against teams from Saudi Arabia in the competition  and are winless in their last four such games. Al-Hilal have lost just one of their 14 group stage games against teams from Uzbekistan in AFC Champions League Elite history, a 1-2 loss to FK Mash’al Mubarek in 2006; they have scored in each of their 14 such games in the competition, scoring at least twice in 11 of these.

synopsis:
The fourth round of AFC 2026 FIFA World Cup Qualification matches take place over three days.
The third-placed and fourth-placed teams from the third round were divided into two groups of three teams.
Group A features Qatar, UAE & Oman and will play their matches in Qatar.
Group B Features KSA, Iraq & Indonesia who will play their games in KSA.
The winners of each group will qualify directly for the 2026 FIFA World Cup, while the runners-up will advance to the fifth round.

synopsis: This will be the first meeting between Al Gharafa and Al Shorta in the AFC Champions League Elite; Al Gharafa is winless in their two encounters against Iraqi sides in the competition  while Al Shorta is unbeaten in their last two games against Qatari sides. Al Gharafa won their most recent home game in the AFC Champions League Elite, the last time they won back-to-back home games in the competition was a run of three games between May 2012 and April 2013; they kept a clean sheet in their previous home game, they have never recorded back-to-back clean sheets at home in the competition.

synopsis: This will be the first time Sanfrecce Hiroshima and Shanghai Port face off in the AFC Champions League Elite; Sanfrecce Hiroshima have won just two of their 10 games against opponents from China in the competition, with a win in their most recent such game. title: M1 -ATP 250 - European open 2025 - Brussels
synopsis: ATP 250 European Open 2025 (10th edition) debuts in Brussels after nine years in Antwerp, staged on indoor-hard courts at Brussels Expo (Palais 12), 13–19 Oct. Draw sizes: 28-player singles / 16-team doubles. Prize money: €706,850. Expect fast, first-strike tennis, sharp returns and tie-break pressure as contenders fight for late-season ranking points and momentum toward Turin.

synopsis:
The fourth round of AFC 2026 FIFA World Cup Qualification matches take place over three days.
The third-placed and fourth-placed teams from the third round were divided into two groups of three teams.
Group A features Qatar, UAE & Oman and will play their matches in Qatar.
Group B Features KSA, Iraq & Indonesia who will play their games in KSA.
The winners of each group will qualify directly for the 2026 FIFA World Cup, while the runners-up will advance to the fifth round.

title: Brighton & Hove Albion vs Newcastle United - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
title_en_trans: Brighton & Hove Albion vs Newcastle United - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
synopsis: Brighton have never lost in eight Premier League home games against Newcastle United. Indeed, the Magpies are the only side to visit Brighton 5+ times in the competition without ever winning. Newcastle United have won just two of their 16 Premier League games against Brighton, a win rate of 13% - their lowest ratio against any side they have faced 3+ times in the competition.

title: Crystal Palace vs AFC Bournemouth - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
title_en_trans: Crystal Palace vs AFC Bournemouth - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
synopsis: Crystal Palace have failed to score in each of their last four Premier League games against Bournemouth. The only side the Eagles have ever gone 5+ consecutive games without a goal against in the competition are Tottenham Hotspur. Both Premier League meetings between Bournemouth and Crystal Palace last season finished goalless; in the competition’s history, the only fixtures to see three consecutive 0-0 draws are Arsenal v QPR, Aston Villa v Man Utd, Coventry v Sheffield Wednesday, and Charlton v Middlesbrough.

synopsis: Nice have lost each of their last three Ligue 1 matches against Lyon, as many as in their previous 11. The Aiglons could suffer four consecutive defeats against OL in the top flight for the first time since March 2003-August 2004. Nice have conceded 12 goals after seven Ligue 1 matches in 2025/26, having conceded more at this stage of a Ligue 1 season only once in the last 40 years.

synopsis: Fulham have only won one of their last 14 Premier League games against Arsenal, a 2-1 victory in December 2023. Indeed, the Cottagers have conceded at least once in each of their last 20 against the Gunners in the competition. After winning five successive league visits to Fulham from 2012-13 to 2022-23, Arsenal have since failed to win at Craven Cottage in both of the last two campaigns. The Gunners last failed to win more consecutive league visits to Fulham in April 1962.

title: PALESTINE, ONE JERSEY, MANY ROOTS
synopsis: Story of the Palestinian national football team, a team that is far more than the sum of its players. Separated by borders, by checkpoints, and exile, the tells is inspiring “One Jersey…Many Roots” them is a single jersey, a shared dream, and a deep sense of responsibility to players come from every corner of Palestine and from communities scattered across the globe. What unites represent their people on and off the pitch that Palestine endures. This is not just in every match, they carry not just a ball but the weight of history, identity and hope. title: Nottingham Forest vs Chelsea - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8

synopsis: Nottingham Forest have won just one of their last eight Premier League meetings with Chelsea, a 1-0 victory at Stamford Bridge in September 2023. The Blues have never before won three successive away league games against the Tricky Trees.

title: Fulham vs. Arsenal - English Premier League 2025/2026
title_en_trans: Fulham vs. Arsenal - English Premier League 2025/2026
synopsis: Fulham have only won one of their last 14 Premier League games against Arsenal, a 2-1 victory in December 2023. Indeed, the Cottagers have conceded at least once in each of their last 20 against the Gunners in the competition. After winning five successive league visits to Fulham from 2012-13 to 2022-23, Arsenal have since failed to win at Craven Cottage in both of the last two campaigns. The Gunners last failed to win more consecutive league visits to Fulham in April 1962.

synopsis: Dive into the excitement of French handball with Liqui Moly Starligue, formerly LNH Division 1. Established in 1952, this premier league event features 16 top teams battling for glory. Champions earn spots in the EHF Champions League, while cup winners qualify for the European League.

title: Nottingham Forest vs Chelsea - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
title_en_trans: Nottingham Forest vs Chelsea - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
synopsis: Nottingham Forest have won just one of their last eight Premier League meetings with Chelsea, a 1-0 victory at Stamford Bridge in September 2023. Chelsea have won three of their last four Premier League away games against Nottingham Forest, including both of their last two in a row. The Blues have never before won three successive away league games against the Tricky Trees.

title_en_trans: Angers SCO vs Monaco - French Ligue 1 2025/2026 Week 8
synopsis: Angers have lost 29 of their 56 Ligue 1 matches against Monaco, only losing more often against Lyon in the top flight. SCO have notably suffered eight defeats in their last nine Ligue 1 matches against ASM. Angers have not won any of their last eight home games against Monaco in Ligue 1, and have only experienced a longer home drought in the top flight against Paris SG  and Nantes.

title: Nice vs Olympique Lyonnais - French Ligue 1 2025/2026 Week 8
title_en_trans: Nice vs Olympique Lyonnais - French Ligue 1 2025/2026 Week 8
synopsis: Nice have lost each of their last three Ligue 1 matches against Lyon, as many as in their previous 11. The Aiglons could suffer four consecutive defeats against OL in the top flight for the first time since March 2003-August 2004. Nice have conceded 12 goals after seven Ligue 1 matches in 2025/26, having conceded more at this stage of a Ligue 1 season only once in the last 40 years.

Gangwon beat Shanghai Shenhua 2-1 in their first ever AFC Champions League Elite game at home; the last Korean side to suffer at least one defeat in their first two games in the competition is Jeju United in 2011, while no side from Korea has suffered defeat in their first away game in the AFC Champions League Elite.

synopsis: Crystal Palace have failed to score in each of their last four Premier League games against Bournemouth. The only side the Eagles have ever gone 5+ consecutive games without a goal against in the competition are Tottenham Hotspur. Both Premier League meetings between Bournemouth and Crystal Palace last season finished goalless; in the competition’s history, the only fixtures to see three consecutive 0-0 draws are Arsenal v QPR, Aston Villa v Man Utd, Coventry v Sheffield Wednesday, and Charlton v Middlesbrough.

title: Montpellier vs Nantes - LNH Division 1 - French Handball Starligue
title_en_trans: Montpellier vs Nantes - LNH Division 1 - French Handball Starligue
synopsis: Dive into the excitement of French handball with Liqui Moly Starligue, formerly LNH Division 1. Established in 1952, this premier league event features 16 top teams battling for glory. With Montpellier’s  14 Handball titles and Paris Saint-Germain's 11 wins, the competition is fierce. Champions earn spots in the EHF Champions League, while cup winners qualify for the European League.

title: Fulham vs Arsenal - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
title_en_trans: Fulham vs Arsenal - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
synopsis: Fulham have only won one of their last 14 Premier League games against Arsenal, a 2-1 victory in December 2023. Indeed, the Cottagers have conceded at least once in each of their last 20 against the Gunners in the competition. After winning five successive league visits to Fulham from 2012-13 to 2022-23, Arsenal have since failed to win at Craven Cottage in both of the last two campaigns. The Gunners last failed to win more consecutive league visits to Fulham in April 1962.

title: PSG vs Strasbourg - French Ligue 1 2025/2026 Week 8
title_en_trans: PSG vs Strasbourg - French Ligue 1 2025/2026 Week 8
synopsis: Paris Saint-Germain are unbeaten in their 34 home games against Strasbourg in Ligue 1, the most home games by a team against another without losing in the history of the top-flight. Paris Saint-Germain have won three Ligue 1 matches by two or more goals this season, the joint-most with Marseille, though they have only done so fewer times after seven Ligue 1 matches in two previous seasons under QSI ownership.

synopsis: World No.1 pairing Gemma Triay/Delfina Brea face No.2 Ariana Sánchez/Paula Josemaría at Rotterdam Ahoy. A classic rivalry: Triay/Brea lead the season with multiple titles, including Germany P2 last week, while Sánchez/Josemaría chase revenge after losing six of seven meetings this year. Expect sharp returns, low volleys, and golden-point pressure in a battle for supremacy.

title: Manchester City vs Everton - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
title_en_trans: Manchester City vs Everton - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
synopsis: Manchester City are unbeaten in their last 16 Premier League meetings with Everton  since a 0-4 defeat at Goodison Park in January 2017. Only against Fulham, West Brom, and West Ham  are the Citizens currently on a longer unbeaten run in the competition. Everton are winless in their last 14 away Premier League games against Manchester City  since a 2-1 victory in December 2010 during David Moyes’ first spell in charge. Only at Man Utd, Liverpool, Arsenal, and Chelsea  have they ever had longer winless away runs in the competition.

title: Nice vs Olympique Lyonnais - French Ligue 1 2025/2026 Week 8
title_en_trans: Nice vs Olympique Lyonnais - French Ligue 1 2025/2026 Week 8
synopsis: Nice have lost each of their last three Ligue 1 matches against Lyon, as many as in their previous 11. The Aiglons could suffer four consecutive defeats against OL in the top flight for the first time since March 2003-August 2004. Nice have conceded 12 goals after seven Ligue 1 matches in 2025/26, having conceded more at this stage of a Ligue 1 season only once in the last 40 years.

title: M1 -ATP 250 - European open 2025 - Brussels
synopsis: ATP 250 European Open 2025 (10th edition) debuts in Brussels after nine years in Antwerp, staged on indoor-hard courts at Brussels Expo (Palais 12), 13–19 Oct. Draw sizes: 28-player singles / 16-team doubles. Prize money: €706,850. Expect fast, first-strike tennis, sharp returns and tie-break pressure as contenders fight for late-season ranking points and momentum toward Turin.

synopsis: Manchester City are unbeaten in their last 16 Premier League meetings with Everton  since a 0-4 defeat at Goodison Park in January 2017. Only against Fulham, West Brom, and West Ham  are the Citizens currently on a longer unbeaten run in the competition. Everton are winless in their last 14 away Premier League games against Manchester City  since a 2-1 victory in December 2010 during David Moyes’ first spell in charge. Only at Man Utd, Liverpool, Arsenal, and Chelsea  have they ever had longer winless away runs in the competition.

title: Fulham vs Arsenal - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
title_en_trans: Fulham vs Arsenal - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
synopsis: Fulham have only won one of their last 14 Premier League games against Arsenal, a 2-1 victory in December 2023. Indeed, the Cottagers have conceded at least once in each of their last 20 against the Gunners in the competition. After winning five successive league visits to Fulham from 2012-13 to 2022-23, Arsenal have since failed to win at Craven Cottage in both of the last two campaigns. The Gunners last failed to win more consecutive league visits to Fulham in April 1962.

title_en_trans: Crystal Palace vs AFC Bournemouth - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
synopsis: Crystal Palace have failed to score in each of their last four Premier League games against Bournemouth. The only side the Eagles have ever gone 5+ consecutive games without a goal against in the competition are Tottenham Hotspur. Both Premier League meetings between Bournemouth and Crystal Palace last season finished goalless; in the competition’s history, the only fixtures to see three consecutive 0-0 draws are Arsenal v QPR, Aston Villa v Man Utd, Coventry v Sheffield Wednesday, and Charlton v Middlesbrough.

title: Qatar vs UAE - AFC Asian Qualifiers Road To 26 Playoffs - MD3 - Mini Match
title_en_trans: Qatar vs UAE - AFC Asian Qualifiers Road To 26 Playoffs - MD3 - Mini Match
synopsis:
The fourth round of AFC 2026 FIFA World Cup Qualification matches take place over three days.
The third-placed and fourth-placed teams from the third round were divided into two groups of three teams.
Group A features Qatar, UAE & Oman and will play their matches in Qatar.
Group B Features KSA, Iraq & Indonesia who will play their games in KSA.
The winners of each group will qualify directly for the 2026 FIFA World Cup, while the runners-up will advance to the fifth round.

title: PSG vs Strasbourg - French Ligue 1 2025/2026 Week 8
title_en_trans: PSG vs Strasbourg - French Ligue 1 2025/2026 Week 8
synopsis: Paris Saint-Germain are unbeaten in their 34 home games against Strasbourg in Ligue 1, the most home games by a team against another without losing in the history of the top-flight. Paris Saint-Germain have won three Ligue 1 matches by two or more goals this season, the joint-most with Marseille, though they have only done so fewer times after seven Ligue 1 matches in two previous seasons under QSI ownership.

title: Montpellier vs Nantes - LNH Division 1 - French Handball Starligue
title_en_trans: Montpellier vs Nantes - LNH Division 1 - French Handball Starligue
synopsis: Dive into the excitement of French handball with Liqui Moly Starligue, formerly LNH Division 1. Established in 1952, this premier league event features 16 top teams battling for glory. With Montpellier’s  14 Handball titles and Paris Saint-Germain's 11 wins, the competition is fierce. Champions earn spots in the EHF Champions League, while cup winners qualify for the European League.

title: Tractor FC (IRN) vs Al Wahda FC (UAE) - AFC Champions League Elite 2025/2026 - West MD2
title_en_trans: Tractor FC (IRN) vs Al Wahda FC (UAE) - AFC Champions League Elite 2025/2026 - West MD2
synopsis: This will be the first ever AFC Champions League Elite fixture between Tractor and Al Wahda; Tractor are unbeaten in home games against sides from UAE in the competition, while Al Wahda are winless in away matches against sides from Iran in the tournament. Al Wahda won their opening game of an AFC Champions League Elite campaign for the first time since 2007, beating Al-Ittihad 2-1 on the opening matchday of the 2025-26 season; the only other time they won their first two matches of an AFC Champions League Elite campaign was also in 2007.

title: Tottenham Hotspur vs Aston Villa - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
title_en_trans: Tottenham Hotspur vs Aston Villa - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
synopsis: None of the last 20 Premier League matches between Tottenham Hotspur and Aston Villa have been drawn  since a 1-1 stalemate in May 2012. Only two fixtures in the competition’s history have ever had more successive games without a draw: Newcastle v Spurs  and Chelsea v Crystal Palace. Aston Villa have won four of their last six Premier League games against Tottenham Hotspur, as many as their previous 29 beforehand.

synopsis: Celta de Vigo have won their last two LaLiga matches against Real Sociedad without conceding a goal, having failed to win any of their previous eight against the San Sebastian side in the competition, and have only won three in a row in the competition against them on two occasions: W3 between 1994 and 1995 and W3 between 1999 and 2000. Since the 2006/07 season, Real Sociedad have scored in 11 of their 14 LaLiga away games against Celta de Vigo, only scoring more times away to Valencia in this period.

title: Liverpool vs. Manchester United - English Premier League 2025/2026
title_en_trans: Liverpool vs. Manchester United - English Premier League 2025/2026
synopsis: Liverpool have lost just one of their last 14 Premier League meetings with Manchester United, a 1-2 defeat at Old Trafford in August 2022. Indeed, since the start of 2018-19, this is the fewest defeats any side to face the Red Devils 3+ times in the competition has had against them. Manchester United are winless in their last nine Premier League games at Anfield since a 1-0 win in January 2016 under Louis van Gaal. Liverpool could become just the second side to avoid defeat in 10+ successive Premier League home games against the Red Devils, after Chelsea.

synopsis: Liverpool have lost just one of their last 14 Premier League meetings with Manchester United, a 1-2 defeat at Old Trafford in August 2022. Indeed, since the start of 2018-19, this is the fewest defeats any side to face the Red Devils 3+ times in the competition has had against them. Manchester United are winless in their last nine Premier League games at Anfield since a 1-0 win in January 2016 under Louis van Gaal. Liverpool could become just the second side to avoid defeat in 10+ successive Premier League home games against the Red Devils, after Chelsea.

synopsis: Manchester City are unbeaten in their last 16 Premier League meetings with Everton  since a 0-4 defeat at Goodison Park in January 2017. Everton are winless in their last 14 away Premier League games against Manchester City  since a 2-1 victory in December 2010 during David Moyes’ first spell in charge. Only at Man Utd, Liverpool, Arsenal, and Chelsea  have they ever had longer winless away runs in the competition.

What unites represent their people on and off the pitch that Palestine endures. This is not just in every match, they carry not just a ball but the weight of history, identity and hope. synopsis: Crystal Palace have failed to score in each of their last four Premier League games against Bournemouth. The only side the Eagles have ever gone 5+ consecutive games without a goal against in the competition are Tottenham Hotspur. Aston Villa have won four of their last six Premier League games against Tottenham Hotspur, as many as their previous 29 beforehand.

synopsis: Liverpool have lost just one of their last 14 Premier League meetings with Manchester United, a 1-2 defeat at Old Trafford in August 2022. Liverpool could become just the second side to avoid defeat in 10+ successive Premier League home games against the Red Devils, after Chelsea.

title: Chartres vs PSG - LNH Division 1 - French Handball Starligue
title_en_trans: Chartres vs PSG - LNH Division 1 - French Handball Starligue
synopsis: Dive into the excitement of French handball with Liqui Moly Starligue, formerly LNH Division 1. Established in 1952, this premier league event features 16 top teams battling for glory. With Montpellier’s  14 Handball titles and Paris Saint-Germain's 11 wins, the competition is fierce. Champions earn spots in the EHF Champions League, while cup winners qualify for the European League.

Only against Fulham, West Brom, and West Ham  are the Citizens currently on a longer unbeaten run in the competition. Everton are winless in their last 14 away Premier League games against Manchester City  since a 2-1 victory in December 2010 during David Moyes’ first spell in charge. Only at Man Utd, Liverpool, Arsenal, and Chelsea  have they ever had longer winless away runs in the competition.

title: Tottenham Hotspur vs Aston Villa - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
title_en_trans: Tottenham Hotspur vs Aston Villa - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
synopsis: None of the last 20 Premier League matches between Tottenham Hotspur and Aston Villa have been drawn  since a 1-1 stalemate in May 2012. synopsis: Liverpool have lost just one of their last 14 Premier League meetings with Manchester United, a 1-2 defeat at Old Trafford in August 2022. title: Nottingham Forest vs Chelsea - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8 - Mini match
title_en_trans: Nottingham Forest vs Chelsea - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8 - Mini match
synopsis: Nottingham Forest have won just one of their last eight Premier League meetings with Chelsea, a 1-0 victory at Stamford Bridge in September 2023. Chelsea have won three of their last four Premier League away games against Nottingham Forest, including both of their last two in a row. The Blues have never before won three successive away league games against the Tricky Trees.

The most famous participating clubs are Al-Sadd, the champions of the last season; Al-Rayyan and Al-Arabi, the popular teams, Al-Duhail and Al-Gharafa, serious contenders for the title every season. The Qatari league includes star names such as Firmino, Verratti, and Qatari Akram Afif, the best player in Asia.

synopsis: Paris Saint-Germain are unbeaten in their 34 home games against Strasbourg in Ligue 1, the most home games by a team against another without losing in the history of the top-flight. Paris Saint-Germain have won three Ligue 1 matches by two or more goals this season, the joint-most with Marseille, though they have only done so fewer times after seven Ligue 1 matches in two previous seasons under QSI ownership.

title: Crystal Palace vs AFC Bournemouth - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
title_en_trans: Crystal Palace vs AFC Bournemouth - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
synopsis: Crystal Palace have failed to score in each of their last four Premier League games against Bournemouth. The only side the Eagles have ever gone 5+ consecutive games without a goal against in the competition are Tottenham Hotspur. Both Premier League meetings between Bournemouth and Crystal Palace last season finished goalless; in the competition’s history, the only fixtures to see three consecutive 0-0 draws are Arsenal v QPR, Aston Villa v Man Utd, Coventry v Sheffield Wednesday, and Charlton v Middlesbrough.

title: Manchester City vs Everton - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8 - Mini match
title_en_trans: Manchester City vs Everton - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8 - Mini match
synopsis: Manchester City are unbeaten in their last 16 Premier League meetings with Everton  since a 0-4 defeat at Goodison Park in January 2017. Only against Fulham, West Brom, and West Ham  are the Citizens currently on a longer unbeaten run in the competition. Everton are winless in their last 14 away Premier League games against Manchester City  since a 2-1 victory in December 2010 during David Moyes’ first spell in charge. Only at Man Utd, Liverpool, Arsenal, and Chelsea  have they ever had longer winless away runs in the competition.

synopsis: Toulouse have won 64% of their home matches against Metz in Ligue 1, their highest winning ratio against any opponent they have hosted at least 20 times in the top-flight. title: Liverpool vs Manchester United - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8 - Mini match
title_en_trans: Liverpool vs Manchester United - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8 - Mini match
synopsis: Liverpool have lost just one of their last 14 Premier League meetings with Manchester United, a 1-2 defeat at Old Trafford in August 2022. Indeed, since the start of 2018-19, this is the fewest defeats any side to face the Red Devils 3+ times in the competition has had against them. Manchester United are winless in their last nine Premier League games at Anfield since a 1-0 win in January 2016 under Louis van Gaal. Liverpool could become just the second side to avoid defeat in 10+ successive Premier League home games against the Red Devils, after Chelsea.

synopsis: Fulham have only won one of their last 14 Premier League games against Arsenal, a 2-1 victory in December 2023. Indeed, the Cottagers have conceded at least once in each of their last 20 against the Gunners in the competition. After winning five successive league visits to Fulham from 2012-13 to 2022-23, Arsenal have since failed to win at Craven Cottage in both of the last two campaigns. The Gunners last failed to win more consecutive league visits to Fulham in April 1962.

title: Liverpool vs Manchester United - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8 - Mini match
title_en_trans: Liverpool vs Manchester United - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8 - Mini match
synopsis: Liverpool have lost just one of their last 14 Premier League meetings with Manchester United, a 1-2 defeat at Old Trafford in August 2022. Indeed, since the start of 2018-19, this is the fewest defeats any side to face the Red Devils 3+ times in the competition has had against them. Manchester United are winless in their last nine Premier League games at Anfield since a 1-0 win in January 2016 under Louis van Gaal. Liverpool could become just the second side to avoid defeat in 10+ successive Premier League home games against the Red Devils, after Chelsea.

title: Manchester City vs Everton - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8 - Mini match
title_en_trans: Manchester City vs Everton - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8 - Mini match
synopsis: Manchester City are unbeaten in their last 16 Premier League meetings with Everton  since a 0-4 defeat at Goodison Park in January 2017. Only against Fulham, West Brom, and West Ham  are the Citizens currently on a longer unbeaten run in the competition. Everton are winless in their last 14 away Premier League games against Manchester City  since a 2-1 victory in December 2010 during David Moyes’ first spell in charge. Only at Man Utd, Liverpool, Arsenal, and Chelsea  have they ever had longer winless away runs in the competition.

title: Crystal Palace vs AFC Bournemouth - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
title_en_trans: Crystal Palace vs AFC Bournemouth - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
synopsis: Crystal Palace have failed to score in each of their last four Premier League games against Bournemouth. The only side the Eagles have ever gone 5+ consecutive games without a goal against in the competition are Tottenham Hotspur. Both Premier League meetings between Bournemouth and Crystal Palace last season finished goalless; in the competition’s history, the only fixtures to see three consecutive 0-0 draws are Arsenal v QPR, Aston Villa v Man Utd, Coventry v Sheffield Wednesday, and Charlton v Middlesbrough.

synopsis: Fulham have only won one of their last 14 Premier League games against Arsenal, a 2-1 victory in December 2023. Indeed, the Cottagers have conceded at least once in each of their last 20 against the Gunners in the competition. After winning five successive league visits to Fulham from 2012-13 to 2022-23, Arsenal have since failed to win at Craven Cottage in both of the last two campaigns. The Gunners last failed to win more consecutive league visits to Fulham in April 1962.

Indeed, since the start of 2018-19, this is the fewest defeats any side to face the Red Devils 3+ times in the competition has had against them. Manchester United are winless in their last nine Premier League games at Anfield since a 1-0 win in January 2016 under Louis van Gaal. Liverpool could become just the second side to avoid defeat in 10+ successive Premier League home games against the Red Devils, after Chelsea.

title: Manchester City vs Everton - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8 - Mini match
title_en_trans: Manchester City vs Everton - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8 - Mini match
synopsis: Manchester City are unbeaten in their last 16 Premier League meetings with Everton  since a 0-4 defeat at Goodison Park in January 2017. Only against Fulham, West Brom, and West Ham  are the Citizens currently on a longer unbeaten run in the competition. Everton are winless in their last 14 away Premier League games against Manchester City  since a 2-1 victory in December 2010 during David Moyes’ first spell in charge. Only at Man Utd, Liverpool, Arsenal, and Chelsea  have they ever had longer winless away runs in the competition.

title: Fulham vs Arsenal - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8 - Mini match
title_en_trans: Fulham vs Arsenal - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8 - Mini match
synopsis: Fulham have only won one of their last 14 Premier League games against Arsenal, a 2-1 victory in December 2023. Indeed, the Cottagers have conceded at least once in each of their last 20 against the Gunners in the competition. After winning five successive league visits to Fulham from 2012-13 to 2022-23, Arsenal have since failed to win at Craven Cottage in both of the last two campaigns. The Gunners last failed to win more consecutive league visits to Fulham in April 1962.

title: Liverpool vs Manchester United - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8 - Mini match
title_en_trans: Liverpool vs Manchester United - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8 - Mini match
synopsis: Liverpool have lost just one of their last 14 Premier League meetings with Manchester United, a 1-2 defeat at Old Trafford in August 2022. Indeed, since the start of 2018-19, this is the fewest defeats any side to face the Red Devils 3+ times in the competition has had against them. Manchester United are winless in their last nine Premier League games at Anfield since a 1-0 win in January 2016 under Louis van Gaal. Liverpool could become just the second side to avoid defeat in 10+ successive Premier League home games against the Red Devils, after Chelsea.

title: Arturo Coello (ESP) / Agustin Tapia (ARG) vs  Federico Chingotto (ARG) / Alejandro Galan (ESP) - Men

synopsis: Top seeds Arturo Coello/Agustín Tapia clash with No.2 Alejandro Galán/Federico Chingotto. Coello/Tapia dominated most of 2025, but Galán/Chingotto struck back with victory in Germany P2. title: PALESTINE, ONE JERSEY, MANY ROOTS
synopsis: Story of the Palestinian national football team, a team that is far more than the sum of its players. Separated by borders, by checkpoints, and exile, the tells is inspiring “One Jersey…Many Roots” them is a single jersey, a shared dream, and a deep sense of responsibility to players come from every corner of Palestine and from communities scattered across the globe. What unites represent their people on and off the pitch that Palestine endures. This is not just in every match, they carry not just a ball but the weight of history, identity and hope. Fot their supporters, each goal is a voice, each victory a declaration. Football it s a living emblem of unity, resilience and the unbreakable b

Champions earn spots in the EHF Champions League, while cup winners qualify for the European League.

title: Manchester City vs Everton - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8 - Mini match
title_en_trans: Manchester City vs Everton - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8 - Mini match
synopsis: Manchester City are unbeaten in their last 16 Premier League meetings with Everton  since a 0-4 defeat at Goodison Park in January 2017. Only against Fulham, West Brom, and West Ham  are the Citizens currently on a longer unbeaten run in the competition. Everton are winless in their last 14 away Premier League games against Manchester City  since a 2-1 victory in December 2010 during David Moyes’ first spell in charge. Only at Man Utd, Liverpool, Arsenal, and Chelsea  have they ever had longer winless away runs in the competition.

synopsis: Fulham have only won one of their last 14 Premier League games against Arsenal, a 2-1 victory in December 2023. After winning five successive league visits to Fulham from 2012-13 to 2022-23, Arsenal have since failed to win at Craven Cottage in both of the last two campaigns. The Gunners last failed to win more consecutive league visits to Fulham in April 1962.

synopsis: Paris Saint-Germain are unbeaten in their 34 home games against Strasbourg in Ligue 1, the most home games by a team against another without losing in the history of the top-flight. Paris Saint-Germain have won three Ligue 1 matches by two or more goals this season, the joint-most with Marseille, though they have only done so fewer times after seven Ligue 1 matches in two previous seasons under QSI ownership.

synopsis:
The fourth round of AFC 2026 FIFA World Cup Qualification matches take place over three days.
The third-placed and fourth-placed teams from the third round were divided into two groups of three teams.
Group A features Qatar, UAE & Oman and will play their matches in Qatar.
Group B Features KSA, Iraq & Indonesia who will play their games in KSA.
The winners of each group will qualify directly for the 2026 FIFA World Cup, while the runners-up will advance to the fifth round.

synopsis: Manchester City are unbeaten in their last 16 Premier League meetings with Everton  since a 0-4 defeat at Goodison Park in January 2017. Only against Fulham, West Brom, and West Ham  are the Citizens currently on a longer unbeaten run in the competition. Everton are winless in their last 14 away Premier League games against Manchester City  since a 2-1 victory in December 2010 during David Moyes’ first spell in charge. Everton are winless in their last 14 away Premier League games against Manchester City  since a 2-1 victory in December 2010 during David Moyes’ first spell in charge. Only at Man Utd, Liverpool, Arsenal, and Chelsea  have they ever had longer winless away runs in the competition.

title: Montpellier vs Nantes - LNH Division 1 - French Handball Starligue

synopsis: Dive into the excitement of French handball with Liqui Moly Starligue, formerly LNH Division 1. Established in 1952, this premier league event features 16 top teams battling for glory. With Montpellier’s  14 Handball titles and Paris Saint-Germain's 11 wins, the competition is fierce. Champions earn spots in the EHF Champions League, while cup winners qualify for the European League.
